            <p>Carbon footprint is a term used to indicate the amount of carbon(measured in tonnes) being produced due to an individual or an activity. The carbon emissions from the combustion of fossil fuels, food wastage leading to more food production, and improper segregation of plastics which end up in landfills all add to our carbon footprint. Moreover, of all the greenhouse gas emissions carbon has a bigger impact on the environment in terms of climatic change, indicators of which are melting ice-caps, rising sea levels.</p>
