        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 carbon-info">
            <p class="no_margin">Food packaging is one industry that uses a lot of plastic (especially single-use plastics) in its packaging.</p>
            <p class="list-title">The three stages to pay attention to are:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Production</li>
                <li>Transportation</li>
                <li>Elimination</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For production, plants are working non-stop to produce a sufficient amount of plastic bottles, containers, and wraps.</p>
            <p>Next, these items are being delivered to other manufacturers or retailers, who may be located anywhere in the world resulting in carbon emissions via fuel consumption.</p>
            <p>Last, but not least, the dumping and recycling of plastic releases carbon dioxide as well.</p>
            <p class="no_margin">By switching to alternatives ways of food packaging, we can severely decrease the CO2 level in the world.</p>
